cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on integrating different networks to provide wireless services to ground users, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of high-frequency directional transceivers and free-space-optical communication modules, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with integrating different networks for better communication, which is the main focus of the communications and networking sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses managing resource allocation in an integrated system, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with providing wireless services to remote areas, which may require distributed, parallel, or cluster computing.
